begin_memory_text: In the beginning we talked about what we do for work - he works in sales and said he's worked for Fortune 500 companies, and I found out that he lives in Memphis which is pretty close by.
middle_memory_text: We talked about Nashville and how it's grown, politics and how exhausting the news is, and the lottery which is the reason he was on Prolific in the first place.
end_memory_text: We talked about video games, consoles, and the quality of games when I was young and he was a teenager. We also discussed TV shows and he asked for recommendations.
rest_of_day_open: I only have one day of work left this week, so that will probably mean that my week relative to work will be pretty easy. That being said, my partner has an upcoming life event that will make life pretty stressful until it is over next Tuesday. As such, I think I'll be stressed about that for the remainder of the week.
critical_positive: I think that despite the age difference, my conversation partner and I had a decent amount in common. I surmised that we probably shared political leaning based upon some of his commentary on politics, so that was common ground. In addition, we shared some interest in the area in which we live which is pretty close together and in some hobbies and interests.
critical_negative: I think there's a component of discomfort to talking to a stranger that I had to adjust to at first. There was also the factor of time, an expectation of a specific duration of conversation changed the dynamic to some degree such that we were both keeping an eye on time while we talked.

critical_positive: i liked that there wasn't an agenda for us to talk about.  we could just jump right into conversation , and see where that led us.   with an agenda, in my opinion, it almost makes it forced conversation.  i felt this was a very natural and free flowing conversation.   outside of that, not having the timer on the screen was good - so we cuould just chat and not change the tone of our conversation.
critical_negative: i thougth in general it went really goood.  there was one blip , where one of our internet connection stopped.  but it was very brief, like under a few seconds so we were able to jump right back into the conversation.  outside of that blip - it was all good.
